@node "hist" "Version History"
@{u}@{fg highlight}Version History@{fg text}@{uu}

@{u}2.7 (2.5.2002)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° The argument QUIT has been added to tell an already running instance of YGM to quit. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}2.6 (30.3.2002)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° The argument NOQUIT has been added to tell YGM not to quit an already running instance of YGM if it is started again. 
° Hitting 'Help' when the YGM gui is active will display the YGM user guide now. 
° Modified the places where YGM looks for different files to better support running YGM from the WBStartup drawer:
- ACCESSFILE will be searched in 'YGM/s/' and 's:' too.
- YGM.prefs will be searched in 'YGM:' and 'ENV:' too.
- YGM.guide will be searched in 'YGM:' too.
- Icons will be searched in 'YGM:icons/' too.
- Sound files will be searched in 'YGM:sounds/' too. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}2.5 (20.4.2001)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° Mailbox login now supports APOP for transmitting username and password more safely. 
° REPEAT values may now be specified in seconds too. 
° When REPEAT and AUTOSTART is specified the mailbox check will now only start if bsdsocket.library is available and the TCP/IP stack is online.
This prevents annoying 'can't open bsdsocket.library' requesters when YGM is running in the background all the time (MIAMI, Genesis). 
° Removed a bug where specifying RUNCOMMAND and NOREQ could lead to a system freeze. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}2.4 (24.8.2000)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° The connection with a mail server can now be stopped *immediately* by hitting the 'Stop' button - this eliminates waiting for a timeout. 
° Checking the current mailbox can now be skipped by hitting the new 'Skip' button. 
° The mailbox status gadget now has a vertical scroll gadget when using the ReAction GUI module. 
° The GUI will now refresh immediately after a resize when YGM is busy talking to a mail server. 
° Each line in the ACCESSFILE may now also contain an 'Alias' and a 'Disable' field. 
° Leading and trailing blanks in fields of ACCESSFILE lines will now be ignored too. 
° Usernames and passwords specified in the ACCESSFILE may contain the character '#' now.
If an ACCESSFILE line does not contain all necessary values (username, password, server) a specific message will be written to the logfile. 
° The argument BUSYICON has been added to specify a different Icon image when YGM is querying the mail server. 
° The Menu 'Mailbox' with its item 'Execute RUNCOMMAND' has been added to be able to execute the program or script specified with RUNCOMMAND if at least one mailbox being queried has new or old mail. 
° The Menu 'Window' with its items 'Snapshot' and 'UnSnapshot' has been added allowing to fix and free the GUI position and dimension. 
° YGM's AppIcon position can now be fixed and freed using the appropriate Workbench menu items under OS3.5. 
° YGM will now remember checked mails by default even when the program has been stopped and restarted. 
° Specifying DELAY with values smaller than 50 didn't work properly. 
° YGM now expects V3.x GUI modules. 
° YGM now expects V2.x language catalogs. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}2.3@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° Internal release. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}2.2 (20.3.2000)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° YGM ran into dire straits when it was started again while another instance   of the program was talking to the mail servers - this has been fixed. 
° The install script speaks italian now too. 
° Italian translation catalog added to distribution archive. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}2.1 (2.3.2000)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° The current mailbox status will now be written to the environment variable   YGMBOXSTAT after each query.   This enables other applications to act more specifically when   retrieving mails.   There are four new ARexx scripts enclosed to demonstrate how to use   YGMBOXSTAT. 
° YGMs AppIcon won't be reset to zero when the accounts cannot be checked   anymore (no stack available, no connection, no successful login, etc.).   In this case the last status will be preserved. 
° The GUI requester now initially displays the status of the last mailcheck   sequence after it has returned from hidden state. 
° The arguments LOGLEVEL und LOGNAME have been added. 
° YGM now is much more precise when deciding between newmail and oldmail.   It will only use NEWMAILICON now if there really is at least one email   it hasn't checked before during the active session. 
° YGM didn't perform as expected when NOREQ was specified - fixed. 
° Some mail servers caused YGM unnecessarily to report an 'error after UIDL' -   this has been fixed. 
° NEWMAILICON wasn't removed when only NEWMAILICON and NODEFICON were   specified and no mail was waiting anymore - fixed. 
° Using the PLAYSOUND argument could cause YGM to freeze if other than the   official sound.datatypes were used - this has been fixed. 
° The installer script now won't overwrite an existing YGM.dat anymore   and it now asks before overwriting an existing YGM icon to preserve   modified ToolTypes by the user. 
° The install script speaks spanish now too. 
° The installer script V1.6 contained a bug when it was used under the   'English' language - fixed. 
° Spanish translation catalog added to distribution archive. 
° YGM now expects V2.x GUI modules. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}2.0 (8.2.2000)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° Various application icons now visualize the mailbox status.   The arguments NOMAILICON, NEWMAILICON, OLDMAILICON, NODEFICON, ICONX and   ICONY have been added. 
° YGM now uses the OS3.5 ReAction gui engine to build its GUI by default.   The argument GUIENGINE has been added. 
° The GUI can now be resized and hidden. 
° YGM now is a commodity.   It can be controlled via the Commodity Exchange program.   The arguments CX_PRIORITY, CX_POPUP, CX_POPKEY have been added.   Selecting the window's close gadget will hide the GUI now. 
° YGM now is able to check repeatedly for new mail.   The argument REPEAT has been added. 
° Norwegian translation catalog added to distribution archive. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}1.3 (25.6.99)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° The arguments DISPLAYBEEP, PLAYSOUND, RUNCOMMAND have been added to   provide various means to inform the user when new mail has arrived. 
° The argument ACCESSFILE has been added to allow an unlimited number of   mailboxes to be checked during one session. 
° The argument TIMEOUT has been added which will be used as a timeout   value when connecting to the mail servers. 
° It is now possible to specify and use different port numbers when   connecting to the mail servers. 
° Installer script has been added to distribution archive. 
° f!gui.library has been renamed to fgui.library. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}1.2 (18.3.99)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° You can now check from AmigaDOS and ARexx whether you've got mail. 
° AmigaDOS script ygm.doc and ARexx script ygm.arexx added to   distribution archive. 
° YGM documention converted to AmigaGuide. 
° Danish translation catalog added to distribution archive. 
° Specifying NOREQ caused system crash--fixed. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}1.1 (12.3.99)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° Internal release. 
@{lindent 0}


@{u}1.0 (16.2.99)@{uu} 
@{lindent 2} 
° Initial public release. 
@{lindent 0}




@endnode
